# Prepare Urban Runner Episode 7 export: copy generated images into
# the required folder/file naming scheme and zip them (images only).

import os, shutil, zipfile, glob, textwrap

base_dir = "/mnt/data"
export_dir = os.path.join(base_dir, "2025", "episode-07")
os.makedirs(export_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Map source files to final names
sources = {
    # Cover
    os.path.join(base_dir, 'A_comic-style_cover_illustration_titled_"Urban_Run.png'): "ep-07-cover.png",
    # Pages
    os.path.join(base_dir, 'A_comic-style_digital_illustration_titled_"MIAMI_E.png'): "ep-07-page-1.png",
    os.path.join(base_dir, "A_four-panel_comic_depicts_a_scene_at_a_cozy_cafÃ©_.png"): "ep-07-page-2.png",
    os.path.join(base_dir, "A_four-panel_digital_illustration_comic_strip_set_.png"): "ep-07-page-3.png",
    os.path.join(base_dir, "A_four-panel_comic_strip_illustrates_a_man_at_an_A.png"): "ep-07-page-4.png",
    os.path.join(base_dir, "A_four-panel_comic_illustration_created_with_vibra.png"): "ep-07-page-5.png",
    os.path.join(base_dir, "A_four-panel_digital_photo_comic_sequentially_docu.png"): "ep-07-page-6.png",
}

missing = []
for src, fname in sources.items():
    if os.path.exists(src):
        shutil.copy(src, os.path.join(export_dir, fname))
    else:
        missing.append(src)

# Create zip (images only)
zip_path = os.path.join(base_dir, "miami-episode-07-2025-export.zip")
with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_path, 'w', zipfile.ZIP_DEFLATED) as zf:
    for root, dirs, files in os.walk(os.path.join(base_dir, "2025")):
        for file in files:
            # Only include images (png)
            if file.lower().endswith(".png"):
                abs_path = os.path.join(root, file)
                arcname = os.path.relpath(abs_path, base_dir)
                zf.write(abs_path, arcname)

missing, zip_path, sorted(os.listdir(export_dir))[:10]
